column5: Got out on the BOG with Jeff "Cpuguy" , the lake looked a lot more different from last year i guess from all the rain this summer the water levels are really high and made it a day of unpredictable fishing, we got on the lake around 6:30 AM and started casting some shorelines and i get my first Musky of the year not a monster but i was really happy since there is days i cast musky lures and get nothing but just a regular spinner bait looking for bass and along comes a musky  Shortly after Jeff hits a largie on the same shoreline  Through out the day fishing was tough, we traveled the lake hitting lily pads which looked prime but held no fish at all, after a couple of hours with out a fish Jeff finally hooks into a decent smallie  after that we went about another hour with no fish at this point i was getting a little frustrated for i wanted to end the day with one bass so we moved around again and jeff hits off a couple of more   and out of no where Jeff gets a big hit and hes getting all excited "Its a Musky" ye yells and what a fight this fish launches out of the water 3 times before landing her and what a nice fish  At the end of the day i finally hook into a couple of largies, i got a pic of one and the other my camera pooped out on me so i think my camera is done in the garbage it goes and off to the mall in search of a new one, this has happened before and i lost some quality photos so i dont want to take anymore chances, heres the one bass i caught

Great Report!!!Thats the skinniest Musky I ever seen! Must have ran like a torpedo in the water! Thats a nice largie too Patrick! Don't know why there aren't more smallies in Scugog. The east side looks like it can sustain a good population. Anyways, thanks for sharing.
Nice stuff guys, That sure is one skinny musky.
I gotta get out there.  Dang work.  Good ones!!!
Great report and pics PatrickG  Real nice chunky bass you got there!  Thanks for sharing Leechman
great report, the Bog sure is alot of fun to fish with all the musky in there.
